SEA AREA FORECAST UNTIL 1800 TUESDAY 25 FEBRUARY 2014
ISSUED AT 1800 MONDAY 24 FEBRUARY 2014
1. GALE WARNING: IN OPERATION SMALL CRAFT WARNING: NIL
2. METEOROLOGICAL SITUATION AT 1500: A DEPRESSION OF 964HPA. ROUGHLY 300
MILES WEST OF VALENTIA TRACKS NORTHEASTWARDS. FRONTAL TROUGHS NEAR THE WEST
COAST WILL CROSS IRELAND THIS EVENING AND EARLY TONIGHT PRECEDED BY A STRONG
TO GALE FORCE SOUTHERLY FLOW. A MORE UNSTABLE SOUTHWEST TO WEST FLOW WILL
DEVELOP LATER TONIGHT AND EARLY TUESDAY MORNING.
3. FORECAST FOR COASTS FROM HOOK HEAD TO VALENTIA TO ROSSAN POINT :
WIND: SOUTH TO SOUTHEAST GALE FORCE 8 OR STRONG GALE FORCE 9 AND GUSTY.
WINDS WILL VEER SOUTHWESTERLY LATER TONIGHT AND MAY TOUCH STORM FORCE 10
AT TIMES BETWEEN MIZEN HEAD AND SLYNE HEAD WINDS WILL VEER SOUTHWEST TO
WESTERLY EARLY TUESDAY MORNING AND WILL DECREASE FORCE 7 OR GALE FORCE 8
AND GUSTY TOWARDS THE END OF THE PERIOD.
FORECAST FOR COASTS FROM ROSSAN POINT TO CARLINGFORD LOUGH TO HOOK HEAD
AND FOR THE IRISH SEA:
WIND: SOUTH TO SOUTHEAST FORCE 7 OR GALE FORCE 8 AND GUSTY INCREASING
GALE FORCE 8 OR STRONG GALE FORCE 9 AND GUSTY. WINDS WILL VEER SOUTHWEST
TO WESTERLY DURING THE MORNING AND DECREASE FORCE 7 OR GALE FORCE 8 DURING
THE AFTERNOON.
WEATHER FOR ALL SEA AREAS: HEAVY RAIN OR SHOWERS WITH A RISK OF HAIL AND
THUNDER.
VISIBILITY FOR ALL SEA AREAS: MODERATE TO POOR IN PRECIPITATION GOOD OTHERWISE.
3A. WARNING OF HEAVY SWELL: NIL.
4. OUTLOOK FOR A FURTHER 24 HOURS UNTIL 1800 WEDNESDAY 26 FEBRUARY 2014:
STRONG TO GALE FORCE WEST TO SOUTHWEST WINDS DECREASING FRESH SOUTHWESTERLY.
BUT SOUTHERLY GALES WILL DEVELOP LATER. SHOWERS SOME HEAVY WITH SOME FAIR
WEATHER. RAIN DEVELOPING ON ATLANTIC COASTS LATER.
WARNING OF HEAVY ATLANTIC SWELL NIL
TEXT OF GALE WARNING
SOUTH TO SOUTHEAST GALES OR STRONG GALES THIS EVENING AND FOR A TIME TONIGHT
ON ALL IRISH COASTAL WATERS AND ON THE IRISH SEA WILL VEER SOUTH TO SOUTHWESTERLY
LATER IN THE NIGHT AND THEN MORE WESTERLY IN THE MORNING.
